            "title": "Jensen Huang raises the possibility of an OpenAI IPO",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>Nvidia Chief Executive Jensen Huang said the recent $30bn investment in OpenAI could be the last before a possible IPO by the artificial intelligence start-up by the end of the year. He said it was unlikely that the plan floated in September for a total $100bn investment in OpenAI would materialize. <br/><br/>Speaking at Morgan Stanley's Technology, Media &amp; Telecom Conference, Huang said the prospect of an IPO reduced the need for additional funding from Nvidia. He also said the group's $10bn investment in Anthropic, another major AI player, would likely be its last in that company. <br/><br/>Nvidia's $30bn stake is part of a $110bn fundraising round announced by OpenAI, which also includes a $50bn commitment from Amazon and a $30bn investment from SoftBank. Nvidia had already said in regulatory filings that no definitive agreement on a broader investment partnership with OpenAI was guaranteed.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/jensen-huang-raises-the-possibility-of-an-openai-ipo-ce7e5fdadb89f426",
